((SELECT ID FROM APPLICANT_DETAILS WHERE FILE_NUMBER = '5993'), 'APPLICANT USED TO LIVE IN THE STREETS NEAR THE HARBOUR -SANZAF DID A URGENT PLACEMENT AT TAFTA -FAIZAL WAS ABUSED BY HIS SON -PHYSICAL ABUSE-HE ALSO SMOKES MARUWANA-APPLICANT LIKES THE LIFE OF THE STREETS', '2025-09-25', 'TASNEEM', 'TASNEEM', now(), now(), NULL),
((SELECT ID FROM APPLICANT_DETAILS WHERE FILE_NUMBER = '6874'), 'I was working in China. I got the Corona virus followed by the Chinese respiratory flu. I became weak and fall down. The result was a fractured back, hip, torn thandorm in leg and right arm broken in two places.          I spent over two months in a government hospital in China. The expenses were high. I could not do the required surgery , as for example they required 60 000RMB to do the back operation. I had to return to South Africa for medical treatment.          My father promised to help with expenses in South Africa. I was trapped like a prisoner in the hospital in China. I could not leave until the hospital bill was paid. No help from my family , that is, my father, brother or sister. The medical insurance had to be paid in advance and then claim from the insurance. I did not have the money. Finally some miracles happened. An Egyptian Muslim group offered to help me pay for something towards the caregiver. I did not know them. The good Muslim brothers and sisters who were strangers came to my help, without requiring anything from me. They told me that it was a pleasure to assist me. Secondly a South African student in China came to know of my situation and contacted the South African Minister of foreign affairs. She applied pressure on the RSA ambasy and they applied pressure on the medical insurance which finally agreed to pay part of of hospital bill.          I am in a wheelchair and can''t walk as a result of nerve damage. I could start a little walking if I get some specialized treatment, but the government hospital in RSA does not want to give me this treatment. However they were going to do surgery on my arm and leg in December, which they has postponed for April.          When I arrived in Durban my sister refused to help in with accommodation. Moved from place to place with a caregiver like a homeless person. Finally got accommodation where the payment is 5000 a month for a studio room.I have run out of all my funds     My rent is now 4 months overdue. The caregiver salary is also owing. I have gone through periods of starvation without food. I am not able to work and have not worked for almost a year . My father that was going to assist me passed away after I came to South Africa. The above is a brief account of my situation. I need assistance soon, otherwise I will end up in the streets, where I will not be able to survive for long .      Thanks', '2025-04-01', 'MUHAMMAD', 'MUHAMMAD', now(), now(), NULL),
